00:19:21.670 --> 00:19:22.990
Oh, you're so crazy.

00:19:22.990 --> 00:19:23.830
That doesn't have to happen.

00:19:23.830 --> 00:19:24.670
Oh, that's crazy.

00:19:24.670 --> 00:19:25.670
Yeah, I know.

00:19:25.670 --> 00:19:26.670
That's crazy.

00:19:26.670 --> 00:19:29.170
Yeah, that's crazy.

00:19:29.170 --> 00:19:32.430
Will the real Clarissa please stand up?

00:19:32.430 --> 00:19:36.240
Hi, Sam.

00:19:36.240 --> 00:19:38.720
Hey, Clarissa.

00:19:38.720 --> 00:19:40.760
Are you sure you have the right window?

00:19:40.760 --> 00:19:42.400
It's the same window I always come through.

00:19:42.400 --> 00:19:43.840
Why?

00:19:43.840 --> 00:19:45.640
You and Eve have been hanging out a lot together.

00:19:45.640 --> 00:19:47.280
I'm surprised you're not over there.

00:19:47.280 --> 00:19:48.640
She's down at the newspaper.

00:19:48.640 --> 00:19:50.080
Besides, her house is one level.

00:19:50.080 --> 00:19:51.800
Why use the front door?

00:19:51.800 --> 00:19:53.680
Why the major freak out of Eve?

00:19:53.680 --> 00:19:54.280
Why not?

00:19:54.280 --> 00:19:56.320
It's not your life she's taking over.

00:19:56.320 --> 00:19:58.600
Isn't that a little extreme, Clarissa?

00:19:58.600 --> 00:20:00.000
Extreme?

00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:00.920
I don't think so.

00:20:00.920 --> 00:20:02.440
Soon the only difference between us

00:20:02.440 --> 00:20:03.320
will be our fingerprints.

00:20:03.320 --> 00:20:05.880
And there are operations to take care of that.

00:20:05.880 --> 00:20:06.720
Wait a minute.

00:20:06.720 --> 00:20:08.520
Aren't you the one who said she was new in town

00:20:08.520 --> 00:20:09.960
and didn't have a lot of friends?

00:20:09.960 --> 00:20:11.400
Besides, she likes you.

00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:13.280
I don't like to be like like this.

00:20:13.280 --> 00:20:14.320
It's spooky.

00:20:14.320 --> 00:20:15.040
Yeah, I know.

00:20:15.040 --> 00:20:16.480
But maybe she's just lonely.

00:20:16.480 --> 00:20:17.800
And if she tries to be like you,

00:20:17.800 --> 00:20:19.880
it's only because she's your biggest fan.

00:20:19.880 --> 00:20:22.440
She didn't stop talking about you at the car show.

00:20:22.440 --> 00:20:23.560
Clarissa does this.

00:20:23.560 --> 00:20:24.760
Clarissa says this.

00:20:24.760 --> 00:20:26.280
Isn't Clarissa great?

00:20:26.280 --> 00:20:28.480
Only she didn't look up to me so much.

00:20:28.480 --> 00:20:31.920
I'm sure that I'll change once she gets to know you.

00:20:31.920 --> 00:20:33.280
You know what I mean.

00:20:33.280 --> 00:20:37.740
I'll see you later.

00:20:37.740 --> 00:20:41.420
If she gets to know me any better, she'll be me.

00:20:47.280 --> 00:20:49.400
No, this isn't the Broadway production of Cats.

00:20:49.400 --> 00:20:50.560
It's a touring company.

00:20:50.560 --> 00:20:53.080
And with Dick Van Patten playing old Deuteronomy,

00:20:53.080 --> 00:20:55.280
it's sure to be a night to remember.

00:20:55.280 --> 00:20:56.200
Uh-huh.

00:20:56.200 --> 00:20:59.240
Enjoy the show.

00:20:59.240 --> 00:21:01.840
So you managed to pawn the tickets off on someone else.

00:21:01.840 --> 00:21:02.720
Congratulations.

00:21:02.720 --> 00:21:04.440
Well, actually, I was looking forward

00:21:04.440 --> 00:21:05.880
to an evening of light entertainment

00:21:05.880 --> 00:21:06.760
with lots of dancing.

00:21:06.760 --> 00:21:08.800
Besides, the song says some great themes.

00:21:08.800 --> 00:21:11.040
Friendship, hardship, survival.

00:21:11.040 --> 00:21:12.400
Survival?

00:21:12.400 --> 00:21:13.640
Maybe I should take the tickets.

00:21:13.640 --> 00:21:14.120
Why?

00:21:14.120 --> 00:21:15.040
Problem, do you?

00:21:15.040 --> 00:21:17.280
Well, how do you survive being friends with someone?

00:21:17.280 --> 00:21:18.200
What do you mean?

00:21:18.200 --> 00:21:19.080
It's Eve.

00:21:19.080 --> 00:21:21.280
She's everywhere wanting to do this for me,

00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:23.880
wanting to do that for me, wanting to be me.

00:21:23.880 --> 00:21:25.920
I mean, she copies everything I do.

00:21:25.920 --> 00:21:27.200
She's more than a friend, Mom.

00:21:27.200 --> 00:21:28.400
She's an appendage.

00:21:28.400 --> 00:21:30.160
When my family first moved from Canada,

00:21:30.160 --> 00:21:31.560
I didn't know anyone in school.

00:21:31.560 --> 00:21:34.040
And then in French class, there was this girl,

00:21:34.040 --> 00:21:35.360
Miranda Farfel Fine.

00:21:35.360 --> 00:21:37.320
Did she attach herself to you like a vice?

00:21:37.320 --> 00:21:39.160
No, I clung to Miranda.

00:21:39.160 --> 00:21:41.720
She was pretty and smart and self-confident,

00:21:41.720 --> 00:21:44.000
and I was a new girl in town, like Eve.

00:21:44.000 --> 00:21:45.960
So what ever happened to this, Miranda?

00:21:45.960 --> 00:21:47.440
Well, I think she sells faux jewelry

00:21:47.440 --> 00:21:49.560
on one of those shop-at-home cable channels.

00:21:49.560 --> 00:21:51.400
But that's not the point.

00:21:51.400 --> 00:21:52.920
What's important is that after a while,

00:21:52.920 --> 00:21:56.240
I found my own identity, and I didn't need Miranda anymore.

00:21:56.240 --> 00:21:58.280
I never looked at it like that.

00:21:58.280 --> 00:22:00.040
I guess I could be a little more tolerant.

00:22:00.040 --> 00:22:02.760
Well, just try to put yourself in Eve's place.

00:22:02.760 --> 00:22:03.840
Look what I found.

00:22:03.840 --> 00:22:07.600
My biodome, the prefabricated indoor nature

00:22:07.600 --> 00:22:09.920
preserve that I designed in old Hitchbottom's class.

00:22:09.920 --> 00:22:12.120
Oh, and the T-square that he gave me

00:22:12.120 --> 00:22:13.360
for a graduation present.

00:22:13.360 --> 00:22:14.960
Boy, is he going to get a kick out of these?

00:22:14.960 --> 00:22:16.120
Have you reached him yet?

00:22:16.120 --> 00:22:17.280
No, I decided against that.

00:22:17.280 --> 00:22:18.240
I want to surprise him.

00:22:18.240 --> 00:22:21.400
So I made reservations at La Couscous for all of us.

00:22:21.400 --> 00:22:23.240
Boy, it's just going to be an evening, huh?

00:22:23.240 --> 00:22:24.480
Marcia, what a great idea.

00:22:24.480 --> 00:22:26.400
Yeah, then I thought I'd have him here afterwards,

00:22:26.400 --> 00:22:27.760
you know, meet the whole family.

00:22:27.760 --> 00:22:31.280
Oh, Sport, you're going to love him.

00:22:31.280 --> 00:22:32.840
Mom, where's the mail?

00:22:32.840 --> 00:22:33.840
Oh, sorry, Ferguson.

00:22:33.840 --> 00:22:35.360
Nothing came for you today.

00:22:35.360 --> 00:22:36.240
I don't understand.

00:22:36.240 --> 00:22:37.640
I sent my letter, air expressed.

00:22:37.640 --> 00:22:39.000
You still waiting to hear from your hero?

00:22:39.000 --> 00:22:40.360
Whoever it is, he probably shot himself

00:22:40.360 --> 00:22:42.440
when he found out Ferg nerd admired him.

00:22:42.440 --> 00:22:44.640
Oh, Sport, everyone needs someone to look up to.

00:22:44.640 --> 00:22:47.440
Much the way you admire spores, molds, and fungus.

00:22:47.440 --> 00:22:49.400
So who did you finally decide on, Ferguson?

00:22:49.400 --> 00:22:50.960
The Terminator or the Donald?

00:22:50.960 --> 00:22:52.640
My money's on the toilet bowl guy.

00:22:52.640 --> 00:22:55.840
Actually, Mom, it's going to be a surprise.

00:22:55.840 --> 00:22:59.160
I chose someone so famous, so influential.

00:22:59.160 --> 00:22:59.840
So what?

00:22:59.840 --> 00:23:01.360
He'll never write back.

00:23:01.360 --> 00:23:02.920
Oh, ye of little faith.

00:23:02.920 --> 00:23:04.560
Oh, ye of little brain.

00:23:04.560 --> 00:23:07.240
Why would anybody who's a anybody write to a nobody?

00:23:07.240 --> 00:23:09.080
Laugh while you can, sis.

00:23:09.080 --> 00:23:11.240
For the mere price of postage,

00:23:11.240 --> 00:23:13.040
I have opened the corridors of power.

00:23:15.120 --> 00:23:22.220
They say power corrupts, but in Ferguson's case, too late.

00:23:22.220 --> 00:23:23.420
Don't worry, Eve.

00:23:23.420 --> 00:23:26.220
Rollerblading only looks difficult.

00:23:26.220 --> 00:23:27.780
Great, I'll see you this weekend.

00:23:27.780 --> 00:23:34.010
Bye, Sam.

00:23:34.010 --> 00:23:36.810
You want to go rollerblading with me and Eve this weekend?

00:23:36.810 --> 00:23:38.570
I don't think so.

00:23:38.570 --> 00:23:39.570
Come on, it'll be fun.

00:23:39.570 --> 00:23:42.210
I've been thinking it over, and Eve's not so bad.

00:23:42.210 --> 00:23:43.610
Well, everything's relative.

00:23:43.610 --> 00:23:46.490
Compared to Genghis Khan, she's an upstanding citizen.

00:23:46.490 --> 00:23:48.010
Now you're being hard on her.

00:23:48.010 --> 00:23:49.770
I don't think so.

00:23:49.770 --> 00:23:55.060
Check out letters to the editor.

00:23:55.060 --> 00:23:56.780
I don't believe it.

00:23:56.780 --> 00:23:59.860
Virtual Reality Replacing Classrooms by Eve Beterberg,

00:23:59.860 --> 00:24:01.340
but that's my next column.

00:24:01.340 --> 00:24:02.500
What's your next column?

00:24:02.500 --> 00:24:04.860
Until Eve Beterberg beats you to it.

00:24:04.860 --> 00:24:07.220
Looks like you were right about her all along.

00:24:07.220 --> 00:24:09.140
The conniving little reptile.

00:24:09.140 --> 00:24:10.900
You can win the Pulitzer Prize, Clarissa.

00:24:10.900 --> 00:24:12.620
Your secret safe with me, Clarissa.

00:24:12.620 --> 00:24:13.980
Trust me.

00:24:13.980 --> 00:24:15.540
I never trusted her.

00:24:15.540 --> 00:24:16.420
Right.

00:24:16.420 --> 00:24:17.860
She's just lonely.

00:24:17.860 --> 00:24:19.220
She likes you, Clarissa.

00:24:19.220 --> 00:24:20.940
She's your biggest fan.

00:24:20.940 --> 00:24:22.500
Oops.

00:24:22.540 --> 00:24:24.860
So, Eve likes my story ideas.

00:24:24.860 --> 00:24:28.220
Well, there's plenty more where that came from.

00:24:28.220 --> 00:24:38.600
You really should eat something before we go, Marshall.

00:24:38.600 --> 00:24:39.840
Oh, no, I'm too excited.

00:24:39.840 --> 00:24:42.000
I can't wait to see the expression in Hinge Bottom's

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:42.920
